In the past our population was not aging at the speed that it is aging now. 
By the year 2010 or 2015 we will have double the number of senior citizens as we had in the past or have in the present. 
We have to introduce new ways to provide services to Canadians across the country in the areas of health care and education.  
It is not a question of simply increasing the transfer payments to the provinces and that is the end of it, the problem is solved. 
