Hon. Ethel Blondin-Andrew (Secretary of State (Children and Youth), Lib.):
Mr. Speaker, I am splitting my time with my hon. colleague the secretary of state for parks and rural development. 
I should not forget rural development. 
We know how important that issue is to all the rural regions of Canada, my constituency being one of them.  
Budget 2000 is an achievement of historic proportions. 
The third successive balanced budget of this government is a feat not seen since the days of C. D. Howe. 
We have tackled the burdensome and ballooning deficit left by the previous government. 
We have increased job creation. 
We have launched a strategy to invest in Canadians.  
Canadians now have every reason to feel confident and secure about the economy. 
